ÚUCM:       Hiya Evil. First tell us a little bit of your Computer-history.
Ú           How did you start computing and what groups you were in and why
Ú           such a pseudonym? Are you really that evil?

ÛEVIL:      Hello MC Laser.

Û           I started in the mid 80's with a Spectrum 48k, and quickly bought
Û           a Spectravideo MSX after that. I really liked this computer,
Û           and I used it almost only for playing games. I did a small glossery
Û           program and did some graphics in basic (with point/lines etc
Û           commands).

Û           Then, I saw "Testdrive" on my friends new Atari ST, and there was
Û           no question. I had to get one.

Û           So I bought a used 520 STm (with SF354 singlesided floppy).
Û           Luckily the games worked with singlesided floppy at this time, and
Û           it took me a halfyear or so to buy a new drive. Then, another
Û           halfyear later, I upgraded to 1mb ram (I still remember the bill,
Û           approx 200 euro!).

Û           That setup lasted for a couple of years, then the new STe was
Û           released and there was no doubt; I had to get it. 8-channel
Û           sound, hardware scrolling etc etc. Well, the hype was false, the
Û           machine was pretty much like my old ST, except that it had a new
Û           TOS version, and from TOS 1.0 to 1.6 there were improvements
Û           enough to justify the buy.

Û           About a year before I bought the STe, me and a few friends got
Û           intersted in making demos. And formed a group called X'press Crew.
Û           We released a sampledemo for the ST. It's so bad I wish I could
Û           forget about it.

Û           Back into the 90's now.. my interest for demos grew, and so did
Û           X'press Crew. I think there were five members as most:

Û           - Dr.Stein (later Criz/2smart4u and now Bellman/DHS)
Û           - Jonas (sorry I forgot his handle)
Û           - Raw
Û           - Evil
Û           - Alibaba

Û           We worked on several basic megademos. None were released. Instead
Û           we put a few screens into the "Friendchip" STOS Demos, although
Û           our screens was made with GFA Basic. I'll see if I can find those
Û           later and put up for download.

Û           Around the end of 1991, only me and Dr.Stein was active in the
Û           crew, so we formed an "umbrella"-organisations with the Vikings.
Û           The Vikings was two members if I remember correct, but I only met
Û           one of them; Loke. The organisation was called "The Complexion"
Û           and we were working on a megademo with STe specific screens and
Û           various plasma and fullscreen parts. I was really looking forward
Û           to releasing this one. But it was about now I realised how hard
Û           it is to motivate coders. They simply fell into idleness and you
Û           could say that X'press Crew, Vikings and then of course Complexion
Û           was dead by now. This is the first quarter of 1992, before the
Û           legendary Megaleif Convention by Electra.

Û           At this time, me and a few friends from The Creators (ET and
Û           Slitsten), The Golems (Toodeloo) decided to join forces and created
Û           the Dead Hackers Society. A few months later Loke joined and
Û           Dr.Stein started a DHS BBS (it was only up for some months, I
Û           don't belive anyone would know about it).

Û           And that's it, DHS have had many new members, many lost members
Û           since then, but it's still alive (a bit anyway).


Û           Ever heard "Am I Evil" by Metallica? There you have the answer to
Û           my choice of pseudo. And if I live up to my nick? Probably not,
Û           I'm too much of a chicken I guess.




ÚUCM:       When and why was DHS founded and what are your current jobs in the
Ú           crew? I can remember that you were not a coder some years ago. What
Ú           did you force to start coding?

ÛEVIL:      Well how DHS was founded you can see in the previous answer.
Û           I'm currently trying to program and paint some gfx for DHS.

Û           We started to cooperate with IMP in 1995, and we were more or less
Û           like one crew then. However, all IMP coders (well there were only
Û           one) and DHS coders gave up after the Aggro-II "Demolition" demo.

Û           Approx one year after Agrro-II I met Gizmo/TBL. Incredible that
Û           I havn't met him before this, as he lives close. We started to
Û           co-work a bit, he made me some routs, I made him some gfx.

Û           And early summer/97 Gizmo released his last TBL Amigademo (last
Û           so far anyway). This had several parts that we haved used in
Û           the Dream Dimension demo as well. It's quite fun; the Amigademo
Û           was out approx half a year before Dreamdim and still it was mainly
Û           made for the Falcdemo. So if you ever see "Panacea" from TBL, it
Û           has some almost identical parts to Dream Dimension (the raycast
Û           tunnel in particular).

Û           To get anything on Atari, I had to start programming a bit.
Û           And to my surprice, ET seemed happy to code a little again as
Û           well. He made a small demo-system for our "4-ever" 4k intro,
Û           and I tried to implement some of Gizmos routs, added some of what
Û           I had done by then (blur, bump..) and the 4-ever was done.

Û           After this ET began his mega-idle which hasn't stopped yet, and
Û           Gizmo got really busy with school. So I had to continue the
Û           programming, and I made one small prod after the other, just for
Û           the practise (chip1, chip2, jm3, xmas97..). And meanwhile I worked
Û           with the Dream Dimension.

Û           And well, I'm still waiting for the coders to stop idle!



