ÚUCM:       Please tell us your fave games and demos on Falcon and/or ST.

ÛEVIL:      I answered this question one time before, and tried to explain
Û           then that my favourite demos are those I really felt happy to
Û           get. Not how I rank them technically or designwise after some
Û           detail checking.

Û           So, I like the Steps musicdemo from Tao alot! I was sooo happy
Û           to hear those songs, his YM abilities are endless.

Û           The Grotesque from Omega was a hit in the face, I don't think
Û           anyone had expected it. They won the Megaleif compo, but didn't
Û           release anything. Then all the sudden, they went to a small
Û           party with this demo, won the compo and released! Cool, I loved
Û           the demo from first sight. Great sync. Excellent.

Û           The Obonoxious demo on the Falcon, and the Autowaschen Verboten
Û           are the ones I got most happy about, no doubt. So they still
Û           rank the highest in my opinion. I know, there are tons of
Û           other which are better technical. It doesn't matter, those demos
Û           made me so happy!

Û           For games; Wings Of Death is my favourite on Atari. But I
Û           played the most games on MSX, and then I liked space shootem'ups
Û           as well. Such as Galaga, Sky Hawk and Nemesis.

Û           On the Falcon my favourite game is Towers II I belive. It's
Û           great fun even if the actual routine to draw the world is
Û           slow and look crap.



ÚUCM:       The best memory you have from your life in the atari-scene?
Ú           (best party, etc...)

ÛEVIL:      I am having the best Ataritime ever right now.

Û           Everything just rules, parties (EIL, IMP..), people (too many
Û           to mention, but most are GREAT pals and friends!).

Û           The online people are easing up alot, you can send a beta and
