ÚUCM:       How did it came to those online-competitions you are running
Ú           nowadays and what other compos will come up in the future?

ÛEVIL:      Me and Setok/Aggression made a modcompo for non musicans
Û           back in summer 1996. Unfortunetly only me and Setok made mods
Û           that time.

Û           After this, there was much talk about a sequel. And it took
Û           place two and a half years later (dec 1998).

Û           And after that there were many suggestions, but it took until
Û           late april to decide the next compo (4col). And right now
Û           I'm getting email bombed with votesheets for the SSD compo.

Û           Future compos are a secret, what fun would there be if
Û           everyone knew half a year in advance what to do? No, those
Û           compos should be more spontanious.



ÚUCM:       Why did you create #ATARISCNE on IRC?

ÛEVIL:      #atari didn't really live up to it's name.

Û           Most people had bought PCs, talked how high FPS their Quake
Û           got. And if you tried to ask them to goto another channel,
Û           all you got back was silence. And if you took it a stake
Û           higher, and kicked them, you were a tyrrant, ignoring
Û           bastard or simply an idiot that didn't understand how good
Û           Quake was.

Û           This was after approx 5-6 years #atari ircing for me. But
Û           enough is enough and I started the #atariscne with SWE and
Û           Ozk mainly. Here we could kick those we wanted and not get
Û           shit for it. However, I see things are slowly going back
Û           to where #atari was when I left, and it's really boring.

Û           Perhaps time for a cleanup? We'll see.



